title: For Sale/Trade:  Civil War Saber
postcontent: M1850 Staff Officer's Saber. Made by Henry Boker, which is "the" rarest maker mark for these swords. Brother of the founder of Boker Cutlery (Herman Boker). Henry Boker made swords in Solinger Germany. His brother Herman Boker imported Henry's swords and supplied both the North and the South during the civil war.   This is an authentic Civil War relic. It has some condition issues, but these are prized in any condition. Loose pommel that will need to be re-peened if you choose to do so. It is however over 150 years old, been through the hell's of war, with battle damage. It can be displayed as is and will look like a great historic relic on anyone's mantle. An authentic Henry Boker saber restored, or museum quality would sell in the neighborhood of $1,500. Of course, this one is in "Relic" condition and I am looking for a small fraction of that due to condition. Regardless of condition, it is still an authentic Boker, and very collectible and rare.   $300 obo  Will trade. I collect military, and like items. Old coins, Contact for details. Own a cool piece of US history here.   I will ship also.

title: For Sale:  Patriot Ordinance Factory POF P415 Gen3 NP3 coated AR15
postcontent:
Up for sale is a used POF Gen3  P415 Gas Piston AR15 - 14.5" barrel -pinned - 3-port POF brake - 1:8 twist - NP3 Coated internal & external Upper - Lower & BCG. I am the original owner and can Honestly say I have never had a Malfunction - failure or jam. This rifle Shoots FLAT - Extremely accurate - reliable and Always goes Bang! It will come as originally purchased with POF Hard-Case manual - Black Magpul stock & Grip- Factory Charging Handle & POF Renegade M-Rail - POF Match grade 4# single-stage trigger (VERY nice trigger very crisp & short reset) The buffer tube - stock & grip are all brand new as I changed them prior to firing the rifle & used a different stock set-Up.

 The finish coating is POFs NP3 which is similar to Nickel-Boron but after researching it, In my opinion the NP3 is chemically superior as it contains a teflon element which is self-lubricating on the wearing internals as well as slows degrading on the wearing parts and is corrosion resistant. The NP3 is not a paint job or anything like Cerakote - it is electrically applied into the metal.  This rifle is a breeze to clean. For the most part wipe it off. The NP3 has a slick feel to it and is Super Durable. Essentially nothing sticks to it. It's still a little dirty in the pics as I'm in the process of detailing it. There are a couple minor scuffs but nothing to the metal or below the finish.
NP3® metal finish offers many benefits. NP3® permits firing for longer periods of time between cleaning, dirt and powder residue have no wet or oily surface to cling to. When cleaning is required, the effort needed is minimal – usually requiring only a soft cloth. NP3® is very corrosion resistant. It provides a high lubricity and low friction co-efficient, greatly increasing the life expectancy of a firearm due to reduced friction wear. NP3® is a satin gray, non-reflective color ideal for all firearms.
